The driver of a VW Polo vehicle suffered minor to moderate injuries  when his car was rear-ended by a minibus taxi and sent crashing through the boundary wall of a house in Randfontein, west of Johannesburg, on Saturday evening. ER24 paramedics were on the scene at 7.10pm to find the 35-year-old man still in his vehicle. He was treated on the scene before being transferred to Leratong Hospital for further care. © TimesLIVE